Wine Aroma Compounds in Grapes: A Critical Review.
Volatile organic compounds are vital to wine quality, determining their aroma and varietal characteristics.
Which are present, and in what quantity, depends on the cultivar, the situation and soil of the vineyard, weather, cultivation methods, and wine-making practices.
Here, we review the literature on the development of wine aroma compounds in grapes, and how it is affected by the above-named factors.
Increasing understanding of these processes at the molecular level will aid vine growers in the optimal selection of harvest dates and other decisions favoring the consistent production of balanced, flavorful berries.
